Listings.Description:
* They might all look alike - but they are not *

Do you REALLY know what you are looking for in a Cirrus ?  Little secret about these planes – how the plane is treated and serviced makes ALL the difference in what you will get.  You want a plane with hard ladings, unreliable service centers, has been run hot, bad FiKi pumps and the bare minimum of care with a short warranty ?  Did you know that if you don’t do certain service intervals your Cirrus warranty can be void ? Who want’s that – and its very common in the listings.

NOT with this fully-loaded, long-warranty plane...
• Lives in a hangar
• Flown by the owner -- Commercial, Multi-Engine, Instrument pilot
• Every mandatory AND recommended service completed by Cirrus or a good authorized service center
• Proactive maintenance: Replaced Bat 1, both main tires, nosewheel washer (yes that is one that is not even in the service manual)
• Oil changes at 30 hours or less  (good luck finding that in other Cirrus planes !)
• FiKi run monthly to keep the sponges wet in the system – pumps replaced in last annual
• Religious about staying below 30.5” Hg in cruise, 1600 degrees EGT/TIT, 375 degrees CHT
* Full mixture flying frowned upon (makes a big difference in life of the Turbos)
